<TITLE> Foreign adviser condoles death of Manekshaw </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 27 (bdnews24.com)  Foreign adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury expressed sadness at the death of former Indian army chief Sam Manekshaw. In a condolence message, the adviser said: "The people and government of Bangladesh will always recall with warm gratitude his signal contribution to our war of liberation and his association with a glorious epoch in the history of Bangladesh's evolution," Iftekhar said Manekshaw combined in his person the rare qualities of a great soldier, military strategist and a leader of people. He conveyed profound sympathy to Manekshaw's bereaved family. bd
